SIMPLE: negatively
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Negatively
<hw>Neg"a*tive*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a negative
manner; with or by denial.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧He answered
<xex>negatively</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In the form of speech implying the absence of
something; -- opposed to <ant>positively</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I shall show what this image of God in man is,
<qex>negatively</qex>, by showing wherein it does not consist, and
positively, by showing wherein it does consist.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Negatively charged</b></col> <it>or</it>
<col><b>Negatively electrified</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Elec.)</fld>,
<cd>having a charge of the kind of electricity called <ex>negative</ex>,
as does the electron.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Negativity</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Negativeness</ent>⟦br⟧
